                <note type="abstract">In chapter two the author presents an edition and discussion of four Geniza fragments of apparent Karaite reworkings of Saadiah Gaon’s Judaeo-Arabic translation of the Pentateuch (Gen 4:24; Exod 21:8–19; Num 8:1–4; 13:1–4; 16:1–4; 29:3–29; 30:1–8, 14–31:14) and Proverbs (23:5–24:6). An abridged version of this chapter was published two years later in Ginzei Qedem <ref target="https://biblia-arabica.com/bibl/8XIMIAS5">https://biblia-arabica.com/bibl/8XIMIAS5</ref>. On pp. 70–78 Vollandt discusses the possible involvement and imprint of Qaraite mediation in the transmission of Saadiah’s Judaeo-Arabic translation among the Copts, and in Appendix Two he supplies a selection of readings from pārāshat Bĕrēʾshīt (Gen 1:1–6:8) in MS Florence, BML, Or. 112 demonstrating Qaraite influence.</note>
            </biblStruct>
